      "message": "Line 648: 🟡 Suggestions - `cancelAudioRecording()` silently swallows all stop failures. While cancelling does not need to surface an error to the user, silently ignoring framework failures makes lifecycle/recorder state issues hard to diagnose. Log at debug/warn level consistent with the rest of this class.\n```suggestion\n        try {\n            recorder.stop()\n        } catch (e: Exception) {\n            Log.w(TAG, \"cancelAudioRecording: stop failed\", e)\n        }\n```",
